[[File:Nordiska radets session i Helsingfors (3) (crop).jpg|thumb|Carina Aaltonen]] '''Carina Aaltonen''' (born 19 January 1964) is an [[Åland]] politician, representing the [[Åland Social Democrats|Social Democrats]]. She has served for two terms on the municipal council of [[Jomala]] (2002–03 and 2004–11), becoming deputy chair in 2008. From 2011 to 2015, she was Minister of Social Affairs and Environment in [[Government of Åland|Åland's Regional Government]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lagtinget.ax/ledamoter/carina-aaltonen|title=Carina Aaltonen|publisher=Langtinget|accessdate=22 February 2018 |language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://old.regeringen.ax/ledamoter/carina_aaltonen.pbs|title=Minister Carina Aaltonen|publisher=Ålands landskapsregering|accessdate=22 February 2018 |language=Swedish}}</ref>
Aaltonen has also served on the [[Nordic Council]], for the Council of Ministers for Fisheries, Aquaculture, Agriculture, Food and Forestry in 2012, and as the Åland representative for Social Affairs and Environment, from November 2011 to November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norden.org/en/persons/carina-aaltonen|title=Carina Aaltonen|publisher=Nordic Co-operation|accessdate=22 February 2018 |language=}}</ref>
Outside her political life, she has also been involved in the [[Emmaus (charity)|Emmaus Movement]] for which she was elected chair of Emmaus Finland in January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://alandsradio.ax/nyheter/carina-aaltonen-blev-ordforande-emmaus-finland|title=Carina Aaltonen blev ordförande för Emmaus Finland|publisher=Ålands Radio|date=26 January 2015|accessdate=22 February 2018 |language=Swedish}}</ref> In February 2016, she was elected President of Emmaus Finland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyan.ax/nyheter/carina-aaltonen-styr-emmaus-finland/|title=Carina Aaltonen styr Emmaus Finland|publisher=Nya|date=2 February 2016|accessdate=22 February 2018 |language=Swedish}}</ref>
